      "writtenOn": "2018-02-06T14:45:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "what use case is this supposed to cover? \n\nsay I want to know the host that an ip address is assigned to. The response gives me the machine name, but does not tell if it is virtual or physical, so I cannot load more info. Would it more convenient to have ip address filtering in host RPCs?\n\nnote that we currently do not have an RPC that supports both virtual and physical hosts. This CL adds a common RPC, but it is scoped to ip addresses. What about host names?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 22,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 22,
        "endChar": 28
      },
      "revId": "c146f6042987cd3b944cc95bae4c3806219ba27d",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1d1bdd4c_25a54c91",
        "filename": "machine-db/api/crimson/v1/ips.proto",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 22,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-02-06T23:52:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I agree that it probably doesn\u0027t make sense to let users type IP addresses here. CIDR is probably also not necessary. Basically, it would probably suffice to have one argument here which is VLAN and that would enumerate all IP addresses in the VLAN.\n\nIn fact, if we add IP address filters to the host RPCs, then this can probably be replaced with a much simpler ListFreeIPs { int64 vlan } RPC which lists all IP addresses in the given VLAN which have no hostname.\n\nWhat do you think?",
      "parentUuid": "b2c37195_61f82705",
      "revId": "c146f6042987cd3b944cc95bae4c3806219ba27d",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b195e36d_79592425",
        "filename": "machine-db/api/crimson/v1/ips.proto",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 22,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-02-06T23:52:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "There probably should be IP address filtering in host RPCs. The use case here is that users need to be able to enumerate all IP addresses in a VLAN and find one that has no associated hostname (i.e. find one that is free). That IP address can then be used in an add-host or add-vm command.",
      "parentUuid": "548e4d44_661920d3",
